        },
        {
          "question": "<p>Water kept in sunlight gets heat from the sun and is evaporated. But how does water kept under the shade of a tree also get&nbsp;evaporated? Explain.</p>",
          "id": 478196,
          "options_data": [],
          "solution_data": [
            {
              "id": 255923,
              "solution": "<p>The water kept under the shade of a tree also evaporates&nbsp;because of warm air around us gets heated from sunlight. Actually, during day time, the&nbsp;heat&nbsp;given out by the&nbsp;sun&nbsp;heats all the air around us. This warm air provides&nbsp;heat&nbsp;for the evaporation&nbsp;of&nbsp;water kept&nbsp;in the&nbsp;shade.</p>"
            }
          ],
          "num_solutions_data": [],
