        {
          "question": "<p>Most of the water that falls on the land as rain and snow sooner or later go back to a sea or an ocean. Explain how it happens?</p>",
          "id": 480084,
          "options_data": [],
          "solution_data": [
            {
              "id": 256702,
              "solution": "<p>The rain and snow sooner or later go back to a sea or an ocean because when the snow melts from the sunlight, the water flows in the form of a river, which also directly gets rainwater poured into it. All these rivers travel long distances to join a sea or an ocean. The water that sea and oceans evaporate, is added back to them.</p>"
            }
          ],
